  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0d9f\u0dda \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd1 \u0dc4\u0dad\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Four rivers of Nanilwala river are washed away",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Pitabeddara police said that five of the 12 people who were swimming in the water at Nilwala in the Dehigaspa area of \u200b\u200bSiambalagoda, Pitabeddara were swept away and four of them went missing and one survived.",
        "The police said that search operations for the missing persons were carried out until dark today (26) and till then they could not be found and they will search for them again tomorrow (27).",
        "The police say that the missing persons are from Deiendara, Porathota, Watawala Ahangama and Mulatiyana areas.",
        "It has been revealed that these are people working in a rubber factory in Midigama area and preliminary investigations have revealed that this group came in three-wheelers and the Pitabeddara Police are conducting further investigations regarding the incident."
      ],
